    • Constructor Detail

      • TAG_ID3

        public TAG_ID3()
        Create an object that holds a null TAG_ID3.
        The call isNull() on the object created will returns true.
          TAG_ID3 obj = new TAG_ID3();
  (obj == null) <=> false
  obj.isNull() <=> true
        To creates a new TAG_ID3, use the static "constructor" : 
          TAG_ID3 obj = TAG_ID3.allocate();
        See Also:
        allocate()

    • Method Detail

      • asTAG_ID3

        public static TAG_ID3 asTAG_ID3(Pointer pointer)
        Create a view of the Pointer object as a TAG_ID3 object.
        This view is valid only if the memory holded by the Pointer holds a TAG_ID3 object.

      • allocate

        public static TAG_ID3 allocate()
        Allocate a new TAG_ID3.
